      "side": 1,
      "message": "Please see my latest change in attempt to address your concern:\n\n\u003e Conflict detection: raise an error if multiple runtime variables with the same name are registered\n\nThis addressed in vars_test.go in the tast-tests CL.\nhttps://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromiumos/platform/tast-tests/+/2902377\nIf there are multiple variables with the same names, the unit tests will fail.\n\n\u003e Safe access: declare a global variable per runtime variable registration and allow accessing its value without repeating its name, eliminating chance of typo\n\nThis is also addressed in the CL:\nhttps://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromiumos/platform/tast-tests/+/2902377\nThe change is in vars.go\n\n\u003e Typed values: declare a type (e.g. int) and return a parsed value\nI have added \"Type\" file in vars.go (see the other CL).\nThe new parameter is used to make sure the runtime variable type is exactly the same as the declaration. \n\nPlease see: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromiumos/platform/tast/+/2902118/13/src/chromiumos/tast/internal/testcontext/context.go",
